The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The Howrah Municipal Corporation (HMC) on Wednesday evicted 25 families living in shanties along a drain in Bellilious Lane, but only after fighting off stiff resistance from the residents and a section of political activists. Civic officials said the shanties, set up on a culvert covering the drain, were blocking drainage. ?The squatters had been living illegally. Despite repeated requests, they were not moving,? said mayor Gopal Mukherjee. The eviction drive was carried out with assistance from the police. Twenty-five persons were detained for obstructing the drive and resorting to violence.

 Transport minister Subhas Chakraborty will flag off passenger transport service from New Town on Friday. Initially, four buses, two of them air-conditioned, will ply from the Rajarhat township to various destinations in the city. The Bharat Stage-II vehicles will be operated by the West Bengal Surface Transport Corporation. 

 At least 41 people were injured when a bus overturned on National Highway 6, near the Jelepara bridge, around 8.30 am on Wednesday. Police said the driver of the Howrah-bound bus lost control while changing lanes. The injured were taken to hospital, where six were admitted. 

 Domnu Sanachalan, 45, committed suicide by hanging herself from the ceiling of her house on Karl Marx Sarani, under South Port police station, on Wednesday morning. Police said the woman had been living in abject poverty since husband Domnu Kalidas lost his job a few days ago.

 Dennis Gulzar, 30, and Sandhani Mukherjee, 26 ? both residents of Salt Lake ? were knocked down by a private bus in front of Nicco Park around 12.30 pm on Wednesday. They were taken to hospital in a serious condition. The bus driver fled, leaving behind his vehicle. 

 A customer service centre was inaugurated at the Cossipore telephone exchange by CalTel chief general manager S.P. Chakraborty on Wednesday. 

 An armed gang entered a shoe-shop on Amherst Street and walked away with Rs 300 on Tuesday afternoon. Deputy commissioner (north) Barun Mullick ruled out extortion. ?It could be the shop-owner owed the amount to the group, but was evading payment,? he said. 

 A bus racing against another rammed into a rickshaw on Mahendra Bhattacharya Road, in Santragachhi, under the Chatterjeehat investigation centre, on Wednesday morning. The rickshaw-puller and the person he was ferrying were injured. A mob ransacked the two vehicles ? a private bus on route 52 and a minibus on route 9 ? and put up a roadblock. It was lifted after police arrived on the spot.

 A fast track court on Wednesday convicted Santosh Kumar Dubey in an attempt-to-murder case and sentenced him to seven years? rigorous imprisonment. Dubey had shot at Rajkumar Chowrasia, a trader in Posta, on June 11, 2003.

 High court lawyers abstained from work on Wednesday to mourn the death of a colleague, Debendra Gupta. 

